^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The point of this hand is to understand some basic principles of constructive bidding. Constructive bidding is when your side bids and the other side passes. It doesn't happen much these days but it did on this hand. The basic objective of bidding is 
a) to bid game if you have it
b) otherwise stay as low as you can.|
PG| ***** 66 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You don't get any more points for bidding 3S and making it than you do for bidding 1S and making 3. And the more you bid, the more likely you can go down. So, when you know your side does not have game, and the opponents let you, stay as low as you can.|
