^B@2^*BMovie Maker: ^*N|cp||at|Clearly the Bergen Raises in competition is for players who play either Regular or Reverse Bergen Raises. If you wish to learn Bergen Raises there is a great tutorial in BIL library at |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bilbridge.com^*N|CP||AT| or at Howard's web site |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/^*N|CP||AT|.

Furthermore, Bergen Raises in Competition is not standard and a few original bids such as Jordan 2N are not available when you play it. Therefore, to avoid disasters at the bridge table you should fully discuss playing it with your partner. Again, Bergen Raises is a complete treatment for raising partner's opening a major and it would be best to adhere to all of its parts. All bids here are alertable.

BTW, you can play Bergen Raises in competition whether you play SAYC or 2/1. After interference 2/1 is the same as SAYC - I am sure you knew that.

And lastly, in my usual custom, the information is presented in a quiz format with hands and the appropriate bidding. I don't know about you but reading endless text lines quickly puts me to sleep. However, the guideline for each section will be presented in a text format first.

Now please click the forward arrow to begin the presentation.|
